  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of total knee arthroplasty is to achieve best patient functional outcomes, improve
      patient pain score and satisfaction. Synovial proliferation is a common finding in arthritic
      knees. Surgeons can't decide if synovectomy is a crucial step in the operation. Studies
      didn't prove the clear benefits of synovectomy. We are aiming to perform a randomized
      clinical trial trying to reach the best evidence in that matter.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
